{"word":"H5197 - נָטַף - nâṭaph - naw-taf' - Drop","slug":"H5197","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נָטַף</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nâṭaph"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>naw-taf'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Drop"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05D8;&#x05E3; - na&#x0302;t&#x0323;aph</b> - <i>naw-taf'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>ooze</i>, that is, <i>distil</i> gradually; by implication to <i>fall in drops</i>; figuratively to <i>speak</i> by inspiration: - drop (-ping), prophesy (-et)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5188\">H5188</a>, <a href=\"#/H5198\">H5198</a>, <a href=\"#/H5199\">H5199</a>, <a href=\"#/H5200\">H5200</a>"}]}